# Insight language & UX

- Every surfaced insight shows its `n` and a confidence label
  (`insufficient_data` / `possible_association` / `recurring_pattern`). Never
  hide uncertainty.
- Allowed phrasing: "possible pattern", "watch this", "collecting data", "no
  reliable association yet". Forbidden: "diagnosis", "causal", "proven", or
  "improving/declining" used as a verdict.
- Calm, non-clinical, non-gamified. No streaks, no goals, no "crush it" framing.
- Never suggest increasing activity. Where relevant, support pacing /
  energy-envelope framing instead.
- Check-in forms must be fast (<30s): slider inputs, sensible defaults, a "same
  as yesterday" one-tap option.
- "Insufficient data — collecting" is a normal state, shown plainly, especially
  in the first ~4-6 weeks of use.
- Keep `/analysis` (confirmed findings) visually and conceptually separate from
  `/explore` (firewalled, labelled hypothesis-generating only — not evidence).
- Mobile-first layout; the dashboard should feel quiet, not like a fitness app.
